{
  "texts": [
    "The teachers addressed related questions from the elderly participants after each session.",
    "Considering the lower physical fitness and organ function of elderly, the difficulty of certain complex and potentially hazardous movements (e.g., right stomping, left and right downward movement) was adjusted based on their actual condition, prioritizing safety while facilitating skill mastery and practice.",
    "Over the course of 8 weeks, the intervention group mastered the 24 simplified Tai Chi styles.",
    "Wushu teachers thoughtfully organized the teaching content and practice duration to align with the participants' abilities and acceptance levels.",
    "This approach aimed to help the elderly master all movements early on, gradually progressing to practicing the complete sets of movements."
  ]
}